# ‚úÖ HTML Helpers vs Tag Helpers in ASP.NET Core MVC

In ASP.NET Core MVC, both **HTML Helpers** and **Tag Helpers** are used to render UI elements in Razor views. Here's a detailed comparison between them.

---

## üìä Comparison Table

| Feature                     | HTML Helpers                              | Tag Helpers                                     |
|----------------------------|-------------------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------|
| **Syntax**                 | C# method calls in Razor (`@Html.TextBox`) | HTML-like syntax (`<input asp-for="...">`)     |
| **Readability**            | Less intuitive, more C#-centric            | Clean and readable for frontend developers     |
| **IntelliSense Support**   | Limited                                    | Full IntelliSense in Razor + HTML editors      |
| **Design-time Support**    | Limited                                    | Full support in Visual Studio and other IDEs   |
| **Customization**          | More complex                               | Easily customizable with custom Tag Helpers    |
| **Binding Support**        | Manual                                     | Automatic via `asp-for`, `asp-action`, etc.    |
| **Client-side Integration**| Less seamless                              | More HTML5- and JS-friendly                    |
| **Use Case**               | Legacy or server-side logic heavy          | Modern ASP.NET Core development                |

---

## üéØ Example Comparison

### ‚úÖ HTML Helper Example

```csharp
@Html.TextBoxFor(model => model.Email, new { @class = "form-control" })
```

### ‚úÖ Tag Helper Example

```html
<input asp-for="Email" class="form-control" />
```

---

## üß† When to Use What?

- ‚úÖ **Use Tag Helpers** for new ASP.NET Core MVC projects.
- ‚òëÔ∏è **Use HTML Helpers** when maintaining older ASP.NET MVC projects or requiring dynamic logic in C#.

---

## üõ†Ô∏è Common HTML Helpers

| Helper                 | Description                      |
|------------------------|----------------------------------|
| `Html.TextBoxFor`      | Renders an `<input type="text">` |
| `Html.LabelFor`        | Renders a `<label>`              |
| `Html.DropDownListFor` | Renders a `<select>` dropdown    |
| `Html.EditorFor`       | Renders appropriate input based on type |

---

## üß© Common Tag Helpers

| Tag Helper Attribute | Purpose                             |
|----------------------|-------------------------------------|
| `asp-for`            | Binds to a model property           |
| `asp-controller`     | Sets controller name in `<a>/<form>` |
| `asp-action`         | Sets action name                    |
| `asp-route-*`        | Adds route values to links/forms    |

---

## üí° Recommendation

- ‚úÖ Prefer **Tag Helpers** for modern ASP.NET Core MVC development.
- üîÑ Use **HTML Helpers** for compatibility with older MVC projects.

---

